div.p:
In about Three or Four Months, as I remember, Mary brought him a Child, he own'd it and got her with Child again, having ſuffered Perſecution for the Firſt according to Law; 
                  〈◊〉



ſeeing the Second Perſecution, he Charged Mary, not to lay the Child to him, if Examined by Authority, ſhe promiſed him ſhe would not, but fail'd of her Word; which occaſion'd him further Sufferings for his Conſcience; which ſo Roiled him, that he put her away, and dwelt no more with her.
